# Find
# $-2+3$

## Now, use a number line tool to solve this addition problem.

**Directions:** 
 1. Open the [Adding Integers Using A Number Line Tool](http://www.saddleback.edu/faculty/lperez/algebra2go/tools/addnumberline/index.html)
 2. To represent $-2$, click the left arrow twice.
 3. To represent adding $3$ (the second number in the sum) first click the button that says "Second Number."
 4. Click the right arrow $3$ times to represent adding $3$.
 5. Read off the number at the end of the blue arrow.
 5. Click reset to start over.

